comment: The sum of the Möbius function over the divisors of ` N ` gives one if ` N = 1 ` , but otherwise always sums to zero. Theorem 2.1 in [ApostolNT] p. 25. This makes the Möbius function useful for inverting divisor sums; see also ~ muinv . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 2-Jul-2015.)
